g.text: Yurgosky commits a senior staff member for two hours per week over a period of five weeks, throughout which, a Yurgosky team member will lead two hour workshops once a week with key members of the client team.

In the workshops, there will be hands-on creation of the database. Between workshops, the client will be expected to hold their own meetings to discuss features, business processes, and key architecture decisions, guided by our templates, as well as create documentation.
There is limited development involved and Yurgosky provides as-needed troubleshooting. If needed, clients can pull hours from successive months within their contract.
Based on the needs of our clients, we offer 3 month, 6 month or 1 year support contract, the hours per month determined by the client.
There is a range of depth of our engagement from a relatively light customization of the Salesforce NPSP to very complex development, custom coding and app creation.

Technology development projects are not necessarily Salesforce specific and can include mobile app development, customization on other CRM platforms or writing code to meet a client’s technology needs.
This is the most comprehensive of our services and most often entails customization of a CRM (usually Salesforce) for our clients.
This option is more consistent with typical consultant engagements offered by firms such as McKinsey or Deloitte and not necessarily tech-specific.

However, this option has also been very helpful as a pre-step for organizations who are looking to undertake a large scale project such as a database overhaul, redesign of a website or business pivot. The report includes a comprehensive analysis of different solutions, platforms, apps and processes.
This service is ideal for a client who wants an objective perspective, audit or recommendation for improvement of business processes, or strategies.
